<p>Stem-and-leaf displays can also be used to convey non-numerical informat=
ion. In this example of valid two-letter words in <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Collins_Scrabble_Words" title=3D"Collins Scrabble Words">Co=
llins Scrabble Words</a> (the word list used in <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Scrabble" title=3D"Scrabble">Scrabble</a> tournaments outside=
 the US) with their <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Initial" title=
=3D"Initial">initials</a> as stems, it can be easily seen that the three mo=
st common initials are <span class=3D"monospaced">o</span>, <link rel=3D"mw=
-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r886049734"><spa=
n class=3D"monospaced">a</span> and <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-sty=
le" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r886049734"><span class=3D"monospaced">e=
</span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Stem-and-leaf_display#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
